modules.description: Parses and validates URIs according to RFC3986, handling components like scheme, authority, path, query, and fragment. It processes strings and returns structured representations with detailed error reporting. Used to sanitize user input, extract network resources, and ensure consistent URI handling in web-related applications.

Converts between S-expressions and URI components or full URIs, enabling serialization and deserialization. Supports comparison and equality checks for URI values. Used to integrate URI data with S-expression-based data formats in parsing or configuration systems.
